# 2. 接客特訓！

Kohane: Shibuya Instrument Day?
Akito: And you two are gonna go help out?
Toya: Yes, due to a slight emergency.
An: The manager of the shop who lends us the sound equipment we always use is gonna be there, but a few of his staff won't be able to make it, so he's shorthanded.
An: That's where Toya and I agreed to help!
Len: You get to help sell stuff at a musical instrument convention?! That sounds like fun!
MEIKO: Yes, but it also sounds difficult. Selling instruments means needing a certain amount of knowledge regarding them.
Toya: You're right. That's why I'm going to have the manager teach me, while also learning what I can on my own.
Kohane: Hehe. I'm sure you'll get the hang of things really quickly, Aoyagi.
Akito: If anything, An, you sure you're gonna be able to explain how to play them?
An: I'm gonna brush up on what I can too, so I'll be fine! I think...
Rin: So, what does Shibuya Instrument Day involve exactly?
An: Umm... It's a convention where people can try playing different instruments and even buy them. There should be a website for it...
An: Oh, these pictures from last year should help! They're supposed to have a bunch of booths lined up like this!
Len: Whoa! Look at all the trumpets and guitars and stuff!
MEIKO: This is incredible! Each type of instrument comes in a variety of choices.
Toya: They all sound and feel different based on who made them, and using what materials. Each one is very intricately designed.
Rin: But so many choices... Finding the right one seems really hard.
An: Yeah, but imagine how amazing it must feel when you do.
MEIKO: I see what you mean. Finding the right instrument for you is like finding a trusty partner, yes?
Rin: A trusty partner! Hehe. It sounds like fun when you put it that way!
Toya: Yes, if it means helping someone find the right partner, then it truly does feel worthwhile.
Toya: (That being said...)
Akito: What's wrong?
Toya: Oh, it's nothing serious... But...
Toya: I'm a little worried about having to interact with customers.
Kohane: Huh?
Toya: I'll be moving instruments around and such that day, but the core of my job will involve actually selling them to customers.
Toya: However, I have no customer service experience. I'm not sure if I'll be able to send anyone who comes to visit us home smiling...
MEIKO: Feeling nervous is completely understandable, since you've never done anything like this before.
An: Hmm... Yeah...
An: Oh, I know! Why don't we practice interacting with customers?!
Toya: Practice?
An: Yeah. My customer service skills are pretty good, so I should be able to teach you a lot about what to do and stuff!
An: In return, you're gonna help me learn about those instruments! Then we'll call it even!
Akito: I don't know if I'd say even, but teaching each other what you can does seem like your best option.
An: Yeah, to be fair, all I can teach him is how to interact with customers at a cafe. It's hard to say how helpful that's gonna be...
MEIKO: Still, with you as his teacher, he should be able to get in some good practice runs.
Toya: Yes, you may be right...
Toya: I'll be taking up some of your time, Shiraishi, but if you don't mind teaching me...
An: *Nod* Okay!
Kohane: I can play a customer for you, so let me know if you ever need me.
Toya: Yes, thank you.
MEIKO: I know. Why don't you all practice here? It should provide the perfect setting.
Toya: Are you sure?
An: Thank you so much, MEIKO! In that case, let's start practicing right away!
Toya: Okay!
An: Thank you for coming! We hope to see you again soon!
An: That's about everything... What do you think? Got the hang of it?
Toya: I don't know if I'll be able to immediately put it into practice, but I've committed it to memory.
An: That should be fine! You can learn as you go along!
An: Alright, Len, Rin, you're up!
Len & Rin's Voices: Okay!
Len's Voice: Whoa! There's a really cool-looking cafe here, Rin!
Rin's Voice: Yeah, wow! Let's go check it out!
Akito: They're just supposed to be playing the customers, but they seem really into it for some reason...
Rin: Hello! We're your customers!
An: Oh, Toya, we have customers! Let's go!
Toya: Yes, let's...!!
Toya: Maintain good posture like Shiraishi, and be light on your feet...
Kohane: I-Is it just me or is he sort of walking like a robot? His joints seem really stiff...
Akito: I get that he's nervous, but this is a bit much.
Toya: (Speak as loudly and clearly as you can...!)
Toya: Welcome!!
Len: Th...! Thank you for having us...?!
An: Ha...
An: Hahaha! Toya, you're scaring them!
An: You gotta relax more! Just act natural!
Toya: O-Okay. Let me try that again...
Rin: Th-That was scary! You literally jumped at us all of a sudden!
Toya: I'm sorry. Trying to do this right is making me feel rather tense...
MEIKO: You'll get the hang of things right away if you keep practicing. Just take your time and learn things at your own pace.
Toya: Thank you for coming. We hope to see you again soon.
An: Nice! That was great!
An: You still seem a little tense, but you'd be perfect if you could relax a bit more!
Toya: Relax... Yes, I agree.
Len: Still, Toya, you've improved so much!
Rin: He's right! Remember how clumsy and scary your greeting was at first?!
Toya: Really? That's good to hear.
MEIKO: Hehe. Nice work, everyone. Why don't we take a quick break here?
Toya: Sounds good.
An: Oh, Toya, can you tell me more about instruments after we take our break? I understand the difference between yellow brass and gold brass now, but there's a ton of other stuff that I still don't really get.
Toya: Yes, of course.
Toya: Also, I can try practicing with this a little more.
MEIKO: Oh, is that a mouthpiece for a trumpet?
Toya: Yes, I've been learning how to use it on my own.
Toya: My goal is to figure out how to produce a tone with it.
Len: Wait, you're going that far?
Toya: Learning how to do that should make it easier for me to explain to novices how to actually play a wind instrument.
Toya: I won't be working in the demo area, so maybe it's unnecessary... But I'd like to take this opportunity to learn what I can.
An: And we wouldn't expect anything less! You're always giving these things your best effort.
Rin: I really admire how you see these kinds of commitments all the way through to the end!
Len: I hope this event goes well! I'll be rooting for you, Toya!
Toya: Yes. Thank you.
Kanade: Let's see... Ms. Mochizuki bought some bath cleaner for us already...
Kanade: So that should be everything we need.
Mafuyu: Okay. Then, let's start heading back.
Kanade: *Nod* Thank you for coming with me to buy these daily necessities, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: It's okay. I mean, I need them as well.
Kanade: Right.
Kanade: Huh...?
Clerk: We will now be holding a special drawing for any shoppers who made purchases at these establishments!
Clerk: We've prepared a wonderful lineup of prizes! You can win everything from gift certificates to event tickets, and even an all-expenses-paid trip!
Kanade: Oh, they're having a drawing?
Clerk: Ah, young ladies, you can participate if you have your receipt! Would you like to give it a spin?
Kanade: Huh? Oh, umm...
Mafuyu: Shall we give it a try?
Kanade: Yes. I suppose we should, since we're here.
Clerk: I'll just need to check the date on this receipt... Okay, you're all set! Feel free to spin the wheel!
Kanade: Thank you. Then...
Mafuyu: A ball popped out...
Kanade: Oh, a red one. Is that good?
Clerk: *Gasp*
Clerk: Congratulations!! You win the Shibuya Prize!!
Kanade: Huh? The Shibuya Prize?
Clerk: Yes, it's sponsored by the city! The winner receives a pair of tickets to Shibuya Instrument Day!
Clerk: It's a convention that's taking place this weekend at the hall by the station, where vendors will be selling a wide variety of instruments. Professional groups will also be performing a concert, and these tickets will allow you free entry!
Kanade: A concert...
Kanade: (Come to think of it, I haven't had a chance to listen to anyone perform live recently.)
Kanade: (It could also be a nice way for Mafuyu to take a quick break from things...)
Kanade: Since we're being given free entry, would you like to go?
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: I don't have any plans this weekend, so if you want to go, Kanade...
Kanade: Okay. In that case, let's go.
Mafuyu: *Nod*
